Multi-Sale Name: Liberty Property Trust Cabot Fund III
Portfolio Name: Liberty Property Trust Cabot Fund III
Property Name: Liberty Property Trust Cabot Fund III
Seller Company: Cabot Industrial Value Fund III Manager, LP
Transaction Notes: On October 8, 2013, Malvern, PA-based Liberty Property Trust closed on the acquisition of the Cabot Industrial Value Fund III for $1.475 billion or approximately $64 per square foot. The transaction totaled approximately 23 million square feet, 177 properties and 24 new industrial markets. Approximately 58% of the portfolio is located in existing Liberty Industrial markets, including Chicago, South Florida, Houston, New Jersey, Maryland, U.K., Central Pennsylvania, Carolinas, Minnesota, Tampa, Richmond, Arizona, Orlando and Philadelphia. These properties were 92.8% leased at the time of sale. Of the remaining approximate 10 million square feet, Liberty acquired in new market areas including; Atlanta, Dallas/Ft. Worth, Cincinnati, Indianapolis, Columbus, Southern California, Boston, Delaware, Memphis and Seattle/Puget Sound. The acquisition was funded through a combination of sources including proceeds of $834.1 million from an offering of 24,150,000 common shares, proceeds from the offering of $450 million of 4.40% senior notes due 2024 and the assumption of nearly $230 million in mortgage debt. The company also borrowed $470 million under a unsecured term loan ("New Term Loan") and intend to sell certain operating properties that will generate approximately $150 million in additional proceeds. A $1.27 billion bridge loan, the company entered into a commitment letter for was not needed since net proceeds from equity offering and borrowings were secured. Citigroup and Goldman Sachs & Co. served as Liberty's exclusive financial advisors on the acquisition. Both Liberty Property Trust and Cabot Properties declined to disclose any additional information on the transaction at the time of this report. Deed and loan documents will be attached as they are recorded. More information will be added as it becomes available.

Legal Description: Lot 1, Blk 1 of Pioneer Parkway/SH161, an addition o the City of Grand Prairie
Transaction Notes: The details of this report were confirmed with three sources deemed reliable. This report details the sale of the 603,354 SF distribution center, which is 100% NNN leased to Solo Cup through 2019, for a confirmed $27.625 million, or $45.79/SF, following 2 months under contract and a short time on the market. It is worth noting that the seller was originally marketing two shovel-ready industrial sites adjacent to this building, but the buyer chose only to acquire the asset included here. It was confirmed that the property traded at a 6.44 cap rate, indicating $1,779,050 NOI at $2.95/SF annual rent. Expenses were estimated to be just over $1/SF. It was reported that the buyer calculated a cap rate of 6.25, including vacancy loss, etc., but as the tenant occupies 100% of the space, research indicates the 6.44 cap rate is a more accurate reflection of the transaction. It was stated that the seller sold as part of a larger strategy, as did the buyer, with the seller moving away from industrial assets in markets like Dallas, and the buyer focused on increasing their industrial holdings, particularly in the Dallas market. The building was delivered in 2008 and the tenant is a national credit tenant. Both of those factors made the acquisition more attractive to the buyer. Pro forma performance was not elaborated on. It is unclear what escalations, if any, are provided for in the tenant's lease.
